Right. The link to the docs page is http://docs.moodle.org/dev/Data_manipulation_API . Their current code 
```text
$sql_query = "SELECT * FROM {$CFG->prefix}plagiarism_crot_files WHERE path ='$path' AND courseid = $course AND cm = $cmid ORDER BY file_id DESC LIMIT 1";
```
 violates the expected API usage at least in the following areas: If possible, methods like get_records() or get_records_select() etc should be used instead of providing the full SQL. This makes the code more cross-database compliant. Specifying full query should be used only if there is no other way. In Moodle 2.x, we do not use {$CFG->prefix} any more in SQL queries. The table name itself should be wrapped by curly braces as in {plagiarism_crot_files} and the $DB automatically prepends the prefix if needed. Variables expansion in SQL queries (i.e. having $path, $course, $cmid there) is a very bad practise as it makes the query potentially vulnerable to SQL injections. Correct way is to use placeholders, either named (e.g. :courseid) or unnamed (via question marks). Specifying LIMIT at the end is not generally cross-database compatible (even if in this simple case it might be) and $DB methods provide explicit parameters for that. So basically, this particular code could (and probably should) be achieved by something like 
```text
$files = $DB->get_records('plagiarism_crot_files', array('path' => $path, 'courseid' => $cid, 'cm' => $cmid), 'file_id DESC', 0, 1);
$file = reset($files);
```
 or, if they really insisted on having the full query explicit: 
```text
$sql = "SELECT * FROM {plagiarism_crot_files} WHERE path = ? AND courseid = ? AND cm = ? ORDER BY file_id DESC";
$params = array($path, $cid, $cmid);
$files = $DB->get_records_sql($sql, $params, 0, 1);
$file = reset($files);
```

Hi Heidi, the prompt way I can see is to disable Workshop emailing completely. To do so, edit file mod/workshop/lib.php. Locate the function workshop_cron() near line 165. Then find the lines 
```text
// Find all workshop notifications that have yet to be mailed out, and mails them
$cutofftime = $timenow - $CFG-&gt;maxeditingtime;
```
 near line 181 and add "return true;" below them so the code reads 
```text
// Find all workshop notifications that have yet to be mailed out, and mails them
$cutofftime = $timenow - $CFG-&gt;maxeditingtime;
return true;
```
 Be ware - by this way, no emails will be sent by workshop any more - even those that would be correct submission/assessment reminders.
